President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation to honor the victims of the mine explosion in Montcoal, West Virginia. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at all public buildings, grounds, military facilities, and naval stations of the Federal Government in West Virginia until sunset on April 18, 2010. This is done as a mark of respect for those who lost their lives in the tragedy. The proclamation was signed on April 12, 2010.